propDescriptions.component: The component used for the root node. Either a string to use a HTML element or a component.
propDescriptions.count:
The total number of rows.
To enable server side pagination for an unknown number of items, provide -1.
propDescriptions.getItemAriaLabel:
Accepts a function which returns a string value that provides a user-friendly name for the current page. This is important for screen reader users.
For localization purposes, you can use the provided translations.

Signature:
function(type: string) => string
type: The link or button type to format ('first' | 'last' | 'next' | 'previous').
propDescriptions.labelDisplayedRows:
Customize the displayed rows label. Invoked with a { from, to, count, page } object.
For localization purposes, you can use the provided translations.
propDescriptions.labelId: Id of the label element within the pagination.
propDescriptions.labelRowsPerPage:
Customize the rows per page label.
For localization purposes, you can use the provided translations.
propDescriptions.onPageChange:
Callback fired when the page is changed.

Signature:
function(event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement> | null, page: number) => void
event: The event source of the callback.
page: The page selected.
propDescriptions.onRowsPerPageChange:
Callback fired when the number of rows per page is changed.

Signature:
function(event: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLTextAreaElement | HTMLInputElement>) => void
event: The event source of the callback.
propDescriptions.page: The zero-based index of the current page.
propDescriptions.rowsPerPage:
The number of rows per page.
Set -1 to display all the rows.
propDescriptions.rowsPerPageOptions: Customizes the options of the rows per page select field. If less than two options are available, no select field will be displayed. Use -1 for the value with a custom label to show all the rows.
propDescriptions.selectId: Id of the select element within the pagination.
propDescriptions.slotProps: The props used for each slot inside the TablePagination.
propDescriptions.slots: The components used for each slot inside the TablePagination. Either a string to use a HTML element or a component. See Slots API below for more details.

root.description: Class name applied to the root element.

slotDescriptions.root: The component that renders the root.
slotDescriptions.actions: The component that renders the actions.
slotDescriptions.select: The component that renders the select.
slotDescriptions.selectLabel: The component that renders the select label.
slotDescriptions.menuItem: The component that renders the menu item.
slotDescriptions.displayedRows: The component that renders the displayed rows.
slotDescriptions.toolbar: The component that renders the toolbar.
slotDescriptions.spacer: The component that renders the spacer.
